50|$|The Force 5 {{is a small}} one-design racing {{sailboat}} that {{is similar}} to the more well known Laser but with a hard chine aft. Although it is designed for <b>single-handed</b> <b>racing,</b> two people can easily fit into the large cockpit. The boats are currently built in Long Island, New York by Weeks Yacht Yard.|$|R
50|$|Today, {{there are}} several major races held {{regularly}} along the clipper route. The Volvo Ocean Race is a crewed race with stops which sails the clipper route every four years. Two <b>single-handed</b> <b>races,</b> inspired by Chichester and the Golden Globe race, are the Around Alone, which circumnavigates with stops, and the Vendée Globe, which is non-stop.|$|R
